 considered what type of game would be best for long term play and for the group at large. Victorian age in the World of Darkness appears to fit the bill.<br>
<br>
Here are the parameters:<br>
<br>
The Game shall begin Saturday night, February 22, 2003<br>
<br>
The players are: Wayne, Dave, Robert, Johnny, Nathan, Ted<br>
<br>
The Sourcebooks are:<br>
<u>Vampire:The Masquerade</u> (Modern Nights Main Rulebook)<br>
<u>Victorian Age Vampire</u> (The hardback sourcebook)<br>
And thats it. No clanbooks, no camarilla sourcebooks, no other-game info, nothing. If its not in those 2 books, it can't be used for character creation. (but you never know what will happen in the course of the campaign!)<br>
<br>
The guideline for character creation are as follows:<br>
Camarilla Only<br>
More specifically, the only clans allowed are Brujah, Gangrel, Malkavian, Nosferatu, Toreador, Tremere, Ventrue. Thats it. No antitribu. (I <i>might</i> be talked into Caitiff, but only for a <u>really</u> good reason.)<br>
<br>
Go ahead and come up with a character concept. Get an idea of what clan you want to play and an idea of a background story to  fit  within an English setting in the 1880's or 1890's.<br>
<br>
Some of you less familiar with the era might consider these sources for ideas and getting a better idea of what Victorian England was like:<br>
<u>League of Extraordinary Gentlemen</u> Comic or Trade Paperback<br>
The Movies <i>From Hell</i> and <i>Bram Stoker's Dracula</i><br>
<u>Great Expectations</u> and <u>Oliver Twist</u> by Charles Dickens<br>
Anything with Sherlock Holmes in it.<br>
<br>
Once you have an idea about your character (clan, origins, background) send me an email outlining these details. I don't need a novel, just a few lines giving me these details (although if you want to get into serious background, go for it)<br>
<br>
Send that outline to me at<br>
<a href="mailto:jbblack@ogeecheeda.net">jbblack@ogeecheeda.net</a><br>
<br>
This will let me take your ideas and prepare a prelude. Over the next few weeks before we begin, I'll have a one on one session with each of you to go over the character concept, do a prelude, and work with you on putting your character on paper. You should have plenty of time to put together something outlining your character ideas over the next month. I'm ready to get started when you fellas are, so don't hesitate to schedule your preludes as soon as you are ready. Just lemme know.<br>
<br>
Well I think you get the idea. If you have anything to add, comments or critiques, problems, or simply "I don't want to play your stupid game, Barclay, STFU" Feel free to post.<br>
<br>
I look forward to another memorable run of roleplaying.<br>
<br>
B<br>
